------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

https://dev.mysql.com/doc/
https://www.tutorialspoint.com/mysql/index.htm

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1) logging to a file

in the mysql prompt

---> tee path/file_name;

to stop the logging

---> notee

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2) check the MySQL server status

---> /etc/init.d/mysql status

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3) command to change mysql root password

---> ALTER USER 'root'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED WITH 'mysql_native_password' BY 'your password';

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4) using a text file to execute MySQL commands.

go in the mysql command line and type the following

---> source file_path/file_name;

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
